SIMPLE: agglutination
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Agglutination
<hw>Ag*glu`ti*na"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>agglutination</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of uniting by
glue or other tenacious substance; the state of being thus united;
adhesion of parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Combination in which root
words are united with little or no change of form or loss of meaning.
See <er>Agglutinative</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agglutinative</ent>⟦br⟧
